cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.GT

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on optimizing multicast transmission in an OFDMA system, which is a networking and communication technology. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with optimizing the transmission of 360 VR video, which is a multimedia application. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves optimizing the allocation of subcarriers, transmission power, and transmission rate, which are related to information theory. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with optimizing the transmission of VR video, which involves computer vision and image processing techniques. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves optimizing the allocation of resources for multicast transmission, which can be modeled using game theory.
